comment: [Observable in enhanced video] Cousins (SAC) moves his pivot foot.
[Detectable with stop watch] Chandler (PHX) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
[Observable in enhanced video] Warren (PHX) moves his pivot foot.
Chandler (PHX) sets the screen on Lawson (SAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Tolliver (SAC) makes incidental conact with Tucker (PHX) that does not affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Chandler (PHX) makes marginal contact with Cousins (SAC) that does not affect his shot attempt in the post.
Chandler (PHX) dislodges Cousins (SAC) and affects his movement in the post.
Cousins (SAC) initiates the contact with Tucker (PHX) and it does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) and Barnes (SAC) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Warren (PHX) runs into Tucker (PHX), causing both players to fall to the floor. Any contact by Cousins (SAC) is incidental.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Booker (PHX) released his field goal attempt prior to the game clock expiring is confirmed.
